Notice the relationship between sine and cosine in this generic right triangle:



[[☃ image 1]]

$\begin{align}
\sin(\angle Y) &= \cos(\angle Z) = \dfrac{\blueE{XZ}}{\goldE{YZ}}
\\\\
\sin(\angle Z) &= \cos(\angle Y) = \dfrac{\maroonD{YX}}{\goldE{YZ}}
\end{align}$

So the sine of one angle is the cosine of its complementary angle and vice versa.

Also notice the relationship between tangent ratios and their reciprocals:

$\begin{align}
\tan(\angle Y) = \dfrac{\blueE{XZ}}{\maroonD{YX}} &\implies \dfrac{1}{\tan(\angle Y)} = \dfrac{\maroonD{YX}}{\blueE{XZ}}
\\\\
\tan(\angle Z) = \dfrac{\maroonD{YX}}{\blueE{XZ}}  &\implies \dfrac{1}{\tan(\angle Z)} = \dfrac{\blueE{XZ}}{\maroonD{YX}}
\end{align}$

So the tangent of one angle is the reciprocal of the tangent of its complementary angle and vice versa.
